osen","id":7102588,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxMDI1ODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7102588?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen","html_url":"https://github.com/jebrosen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-10-17T19:48:35Z","updated_at":"2021-10-17T19:48:35Z","body":"> This is due to Windows' support for paths like `D:test.txt`, which are relative despite referring to a drive\r\n\r\n*heavy sigh*.\r\n\r\nThis \"feature\" seems to cause a lot more confusion and pain than anything else, especially given that [only cmd.exe actually keeps track of the current directories on previous drives anyway](https://devblogs.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20101011-00/?p=12563).\r\n\r\n> Rocket needs to validate segments more - a possible but perhaps overbearing fix would be to simply disallow : in paths everywhere rather than just at the end.\r\n\r\nThis sounds right, at least on Windows. In addition to the drive designation, Windows uses `:` to designate alternate data streams. It seems that Rocket's current segment parsing code also allows a few other characters that are illegal in Windows paths - maybe those should be forbidden as well, although I expect those to all result in errors instead of traversal attacks.","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","reactions":{"url"